    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>steak[s]</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>sweet potato[es]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>into small, bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sizzlin-cajun-style-steak-with-sweet-potato-mash/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>sweet potato</strong> to a pot of<strong> boiled water</strong> over a high heat and cook for 10-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once done, drain and return to the pot</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sizzlin-cajun-style-steak-with-sweet-potato-mash/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil a kettle</p><p>Combine your <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong> and <strong>ground cumin</strong> to a plate with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>Cajun-style spice mix</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> rump steak[s]</strong> to the<strong> Cajun-style spice mix</strong> and rub until fully coated</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sizzlin-cajun-style-steak-with-sweet-potato-mash/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and once hot, add the <strong>seasoned</strong> <strong>steak[s]</strong></p><p>For rare, cook for 2 min max on each side; for medium-rare, cook for 2-3 min on each side; for medium, cook for 3-4 min on each side</p><p>Once done, transfer the <strong>steak</strong> to a clean plate to rest \u2013 this is your <strong>Cajun-style steak</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sizzlin-cajun-style-steak-with-sweet-potato-mash/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your<strong> sugar snap peas</strong> on the diagonal and add them to a heat-proof bowl</p><p>Cover the <strong>chopped sugar snap peas</strong> in <strong>boiled water</strong> and set aside for 7-8 min or until softened slightly</p><p>Once done, drain and return them to the bowl</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sizzlin-cajun-style-steak-with-sweet-potato-mash/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the steak is resting, add your <strong>soy sauce</strong> to the pan with a splash of<strong> boiled water</strong> and cook for 1 min or until the sauce has thickened slightly \u2013 this is your<strong> sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sizzlin-cajun-style-steak-with-sweet-potato-mash/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to the drained sweet potato and mash until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>sweet potato mash</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sizzlin-cajun-style-steak-with-sweet-potato-mash/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Pour any <strong>resting juices</strong> into the<strong> </strong>sauce</p><p>Slice the <strong>rested steak </strong>finely on a clean board, then serve it with the <strong>sweet potato mash</strong> and <strong>sugar snap peas </strong>to the side</p><p>Crumble over your <strong>feta</strong> and spoon the<strong> sauce</strong> over everything</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
